		    <td rowspan="3" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		    <td rowspan="3" bgcolor="white" valign="top">
		      <center><h2><font color="#8B4513">What is TCS?</font></h2></center>
		      <table bgcolor="white">
			  <tbody><tr>
			    <td>
			      <p align="justify">TCS is an alignment evaluation score that mes it possible to identify the positions most likely to be structuraly correct as well most likely to yield an improved phylogenetic tree. The TCS evaluation and filtering procedure is implemented in the T-Coffee package and can be used to evaluate and filter any third party multiple sequence alignment (including T-Coffee of course!).</p>
			      <p>A pre-print is available <a target="_blank" href="http://www.tcoffee.org/Publications/Pdf/062-MBE-TCS.preprint.pdf">here</a>.</p>
			      <p>A powerpoint is available <a target="_blank" href="201403_TCS_MBE.pptx">here</a>.</p>
			    </td>
			  </tr>
		      </tbody></table>
		      
		    </td>
		    
		    <td colspan="1" rowspan="3" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		    <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" bgcolor="white">
		      <center><h2><font color="#8B4513"><a name="SERVERS">SERVERS</a></font></h2></center>
		      <table bgcolor="white">
			
			  <tbody><tr><td>
			      <ul>
				<li><a href="http://tcoffee.crg.cat/tcs">http://tcoffee.crg.cat/tcs</a></li>
			      </ul>
			    </td></tr>
		      </tbody></table>
		    </td><td rowspan="3" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		  </tr>
		  
		  <tr>
		    <td bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		  </tr>
		  
		  <tr>
		    <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" bgcolor="white">
		      <center><h2><font color="#8B4513"><a name="DOWNLOAD">DOWNLOAD</a></font></h2></center>
		      <table bgcolor="white">
			  <tbody><tr><td>
			      <ul>
				<li>The tcs evaluation is a special mode of T-Coffee. Download the latest T-Coffee version <a href="http://www.tcoffee.org/Projects/tcoffee/index.html#DOWNLOAD">here</a>.</li>
				</ul>
			      </td></tr>
			  </tbody></table>
		      </td>
		    </tr>
		    
		    <tr>
		      <td colspan="5" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		    </tr>
		    <tr>
		      <td bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		      <td colspan="3" bgcolor="white" valign="top">
			<center><h2><font color="#8B4513"><a name="INSTALLATION">INSTALLATION</a></font></h2></center>
			<table bgcolor="white">
			  <tbody><tr>
			      <td>
				<p align="justify">Follow the standard T-Coffee <a href="http://www.tcoffee.org/Projects/tcoffee/index.html#INSTALLATION">installation procedure</a>.</p>
			      </td>
			    </tr>
			  </tbody></table>
		      </td>
		      <td bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		    </tr>
		  
		    <tr>
		    <td bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		      <td colspan="3" bgcolor="white" valign="top">
			<center><h2><font color="#8B4513"><a name="INSTALLATION">USAGE</a></font></h2></center>
			<table bgcolor="white">
			  <tbody>
			    <tr>
			      <td>
				<p>TCS is meant to allow filtering and wieighting of individual alignment position according to their reliability. It can be triggered from T-Coffee or from seq_reformat. A few examples are given below:
				</p>
				<tr><td bgcolor="grey"></td></tr>
				<tr>
				  <td>Evaluate a pre-computed MSA with TCS</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
				  <td>
				    <code> t_coffee -infile <i>BB11001.aln</i> -evaluate -output aln, score_ascii, score_html</code>
				  </td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					      <td>
						The <i>.aln</i>file contains your evaluated MSA (score). The <i>.score_ascii</i> contains an ascii coded file that can be used for further reformating with seq_reformat (see below). The <i>score_html</i> contains a file that can used for graphic displax, like the one below.
					      </td>
					    </tr>
					    <tr>
					      <td bgcolor="grey"></td>
					    </tr>
					    

					    <tr>
				    <td>This protocol corresponds to the original T-Coffee. It involves computing all pairwise alignments using ClustalW and Lalign, type</td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>
				      <code> t_coffee -infile <i>BB11001.aln</i> -evaluate -method clustalw_pair,lalign_id_pair</code>
				    </td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td colspan="3" bgcolor="grey"></td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>This protocol uses the procedure developed for the Ensembl Compara pipeline and relies on generating MSAs using fast aligners: MAFFT, MUSCLE and Kalign, type</td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>
				      <code> t_coffee -infile <i>BB11001.aln</i> -evaluate -method kafft_msa,kalign_msa,muscle_msa</code>
				    </td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td colspan="3" bgcolor="grey"></td>
				  </tr>
			      </tbody></table>
				
				
			    </td>
			  </tr>
		      </tbody></table>
		    </td>
		    <td bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		  </tr>
		    
		    


		  
		  <tr>
		    <td colspan="5" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td colspan="1" rowspan="5" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		    <td colspan="1" rowspan="5" bgcolor="white" valign="top">
		      <center><h2><font color="#8B4513"><a name="OUTPUT">OUTPUT</a></font></h2></center>
		      <center><table bgcolor="white">
			    <tbody>
			      <tr>
			      <td>
				<p align="justify">Given an alignment file <a href='BB11001.aln' target='_blank'>BB11001.aln</a>, TCS outputs a file named <code>BB11001.score_html</code> that contains a color coded indicating the agreement between the library and the considered alignment. Red brick regions are in perfect transitive consistant relation between the library and the the input alignment, while blue regions have a very poor agreement.
				Red brick regions can safely be assumed to be trusted while blue regions should be discarted. Green and Yellow regions should also be used with caution, especially when reconstructing a tree or building a profile. The top of the output provides the average conistency (0-100) for each sequence, thus indicating wether some sequences may have a less reliable alignment. A score lower than 50 should be considered poor.</p>
				<img border="0" src="F4_scoreHtml.jpg">
			      </td>
			    </tr>
			    <tr>
			      <td>
				<p align="justify">Besides .score_html, there are other detailed outputs:				
				  <ul>
				    <li> <i>score_ascii</i> : contains ascii format for score_html.
				    <li> <i>score_pdf</i> : will transfer score_html into pdf format.
				    <li> <i>sp_ascii</i> : is a format reporting the TCS score of every aligned pair in the target MSA.
				    <li> <i>tcs_column_filter2</i> : outputs an MSA in which columns having ColumnTCS lower than 2 are removed.
				    <li> <i>tcs_weighted</i> : outputs an MSA in which columns are duplicated according to their ColumnTCS weight.
				    <li> <i>tcs_replicate100</i> : outputs 100 replicate MSAs in which columns are randomly drawn according to their weights.
				</ul>
			      </td>
			    </tr>  
			      
			</tbody></table></center>
		    </td>
		    <td colspan="1" rowspan="5" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
		    <td colspan="1" bgcolor="white" valign="top">
		      <center><h2><font color="#8B4513"><a name="COMMANDS">DOCUMENTATION</a></font></h2></center>
		      <table bgcolor="white">
			  <tbody><tr>
			    <td>
			      <p>The full documentation is on the <a href="http://www.tcoffee.org/Projects/tcs/index.html#DOCUMENTATION">T-Coffee Homepage</a>. But the following shortcuts may be useful.</p>
			      <table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" bgcolor="white">
				  <tbody><tr>
				    <td bgcolor="grey"></td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>To run the current default T-Coffee whose libraries are populated using the ProbCons pair-HMM, type</td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>
				      <code> t_coffee -infile <i>BB11001.aln</i> -evaluate -method proba_pair</code>
				    </td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td bgcolor="grey"></td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>This protocol corresponds to the original T-Coffee. It involves computing all pairwise alignments using ClustalW and Lalign, type</td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>
				      <code> t_coffee -infile <i>BB11001.aln</i> -evaluate -method clustalw_pair,lalign_id_pair</code>
				    </td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td colspan="3" bgcolor="grey"></td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>This protocol uses the procedure developed for the Ensembl Compara pipeline and relies on generating MSAs using fast aligners: MAFFT, MUSCLE and Kalign, type</td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td>
				      <code> t_coffee -infile <i>BB11001.aln</i> -evaluate -method kafft_msa,kalign_msa,muscle_msa</code>
				    </td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td colspan="3" bgcolor="grey"></td>
				  </tr>
			      </tbody></table>
			      
			    </td>
			  </tr>
		      </tbody></table>
		    </td>
		    <td colspan="1" rowspan="5" bgcolor="#FFEBCD"><br></td>
